<h2>Sustainable agriculture (SA) = agro forestry, organic farming, crop rotation, mulching, precision agriculture, conservation agri</h2>
<p>circle of dual effect = agri affects climate which affects agri&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://e7.pngegg.com/pngimages/240/14/png-clipart-semicircle-arrow-clockwise-arrows-circle-arrows-circle-shape-thumbnail.png" style="height:40px; width:40px" /><br />
Organic farming = only 2% of net sown area.&nbsp; Agriculture contributes to <span style="color:#2ecc71">14%</span> of GHG emissions.</p>
<h3>SA for SDG-2&nbsp; (sustainable, nutritious, resilient food systems for reducing hunger)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Climate smart + Diversified (millet, consumer behaviour) + resilient to inflation / shortage / food wastage (40%)</li></ul>
<h3>Why SA not picking up?&nbsp;</h3>
<p><br />
1. 0.8% of min agri budget to SA&nbsp;<br />
2. awareness&nbsp;<br />
3. lack of marketing support to organic etc. - to command premium in market.<br />
4. lack of govt support for ecosystem services to boost farm productivity</p>
